SUMMARY:Son et Solidarité: Sounds for Palestine Marché d'art et d'action
  solidaire
LOCATION:4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)
DESCRIPTION:2026-06-21 17:30:00\n\n4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)\n\nhtt
 ps://www.openstreetmap.org/way/352197557\n\nSuoni per il Popolo &amp\; UJP
 O présentent : Son et Solidarité : Sounds for Palestine Une soirée plac
 ée sous le signe de la musique et de la solidarité au profit du Conserva
 toire de musique Edward Said et du Fonds Elham\nMARCHÉ DE SOLIDARITÉ ART
  &amp\; ACTION\nAvant le spectacle Son et Solidarité : Sounds for Palesti
 ne\, venez soutenir les artistes et les militant.e.s à notre marché de s
 olidarité Art &amp\; Action. Tous les fonds récoltés seront versés au 
 Conservatoire de musique Edward Said et au Fonds Elham\, qui viennent dire
 ctement en aide aux Palestinien.ne.s en Palestine.\nAvec des artistes et d
 es militant.e.s :\nSeif Hajem · Asma Bari · Amine Masmoudi · Fermons le
  bureau de la honte · Lelelines · Stefan Christoff · Regards Palestinie
 ns · Popolo Press · Rickie Leach · Sletate\nMusicians for Palestine Mon
 tréal · UJPO · Levantina Shop · Kufiya Souk et bien d’autres encore 
 !\nLA SALA ROSSA RESTO 21 juin 17h30-19h30 GRATUIT\nSuoni per il Popolo &a
 mp\; UJPO present: Son et Solidarité: Sounds for Palestine A night of Sou
 nd and Solidarity to benefit the Edward Said Music Conservatory and the El
 ham Fund\nART &amp\; ACTION SOLIDARITY MARKET\nBefore the Son et Solidarit
 é: Sounds for Palestine show come support artists and activists at our Ar
 t and Action Solidarity Market. All funds raised will go to benefit the Ed
 ward Said Music Conservatory and the Elham Fund who directly support Pales
 tinians in Palestine.\nWith Artistis and Activists:\nSeif Hajem · Asma Ba
 ri · Amine Masmoudi · Fermons le bureau de la honte · Lelelines · Stef
 an Christoff · Regards Palestiniens · Popolo Press · Rickie Leach · Sl
 etate\nMusicians for Palestine Montréal · UJPO · Levantina Shop · Kufi
 ya Souk and more!\nLA SALA ROSSA RESTO June 21 17h30-19h30 FREE\n&nbsp\;
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/352197557
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-22
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260615T043340
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260622T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260622T220000
SUMMARY:The Social Production of Science reading group - the Biotechnology
  Industry
LOCATION:(online)
DESCRIPTION:2026-06-22 20:00:00\n\n(online)\n\nIn this month's module of t
 he Social Production of Science reading group\, we will look at the Biotec
 hnology Industry. The discussion will take place on Monday\, June 22nd at 
 8 pm EDT on zoom.\nWe will be discussing two readings\, including our firs
 t piece of fiction!\n• Chapter 2 of Living Factories by Kenneth Fish\n
 • Oryx and Crake by Margaret Atwood\nRegister at the link in our bio to 
 get access to the readings and sign up for updates! We will send out email
 s with the discussion questions and zoom links.\nAll members\, new and old
 \, are invited to join this online reading group exploring The Social Prod
 uction of Science curriculum. This reading group continues SftP's traditio
 n of running a reading group alongside our local organising\, and the goal
  of this series is to better link our collective education with collective
  action\, bringing together members to deepen our shared understanding of 
 science\, power\, and liberation.\nDeveloped and maintained by the Science
  for the People\n- New Haven Chapter (also thanks to @sftpnhv for the grap
 hic!) \, this curriculum investigates how Marxism\, science\, and capitali
 sm intersect - and how these forces shape both knowledge and the material 
 conditions of our world. Through discussion and reflection\, we'll conside
 r what it means to reclaim science as a tool for social transformation.
END:VEVENT
