BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-35
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260615T043340
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260701T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260701T230000
SUMMARY:Cinéma sous les étoiles : Occupations
LOCATION:(métro Laurier)
DESCRIPTION:2026-07-01 21:00:00\n\n(métro Laurier)\n\nhttps://www.openstr
 eetmap.org/way/65067662\n\nOccupations est un documentaire révolutionnair
 e qui retrace l’occupation organisée à l'université Columbia\, à New
  York\, en solidarité avec Gaza et la mobilisation étudiante nationale q
 u'elle a déclenchée. À travers des images exclusives et des entretiens 
 intimes\, Occupations offre un regard sans précédent sur l'un des mouvem
 ents étudiants les plus importants de l'histoire moderne. Le film illustr
 e la passion\, la résistance et les défis auxquels ont été confronté
 ·es les étudiant·es qui ont tout risqué pour réclamer justice.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/65067662
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-36
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260615T043340
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260702T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260702T230000
SUMMARY:Cinéma sous les étoiles : Les blues du bleuet
LOCATION:(métro Iberville)
DESCRIPTION:2026-07-02 21:00:00\n\n(métro Iberville)\n\nhttps://www.opens
 treetmap.org/way/47345798\n\nL’été au Lac-Saint-Jean\, les champs se t
 eintent de bleu. Les cueilleurs et les cueilleuses de tout acabit s’empr
 essent de ramasser les bleuets avant le premier gel d’automne. Dans un b
 allet de gestes répétés\, les langues se délient. Les blues du bleuet&
 nbsp\;célèbre un territoire et les personnes qui s’y relient à traver
 s les générations et les cultures. Ensemble\, elles apprennent à se ré
 inventer\, comme les bleuets naissent des forêts brûlées.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/47345798
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-37
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260615T043340
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260703T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260703T200000
SUMMARY:DULF Benefit gig + BBQ + Raffle
LOCATION:4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)
DESCRIPTION:2026-07-03 18:00:00\n\n4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)\n\nhtt
 ps://www.openstreetmap.org/way/352197557\n\nhttps://dulf.ca/\n&nbsp\;\nBet
 ween August 2022 and October 2023\, the Drug User Liberation Front’s Com
 passion Club and Fulfillment Centre (DULF CC&amp\;FC) emerged as a groundb
 reaking initiative and research endeavor dedicated to combating escalating
  overdose deaths in Vancouver’s Downtown Eastside (DTES). As the first o
 f its kind\, this pioneering model operated as a non-profit\, low-barrier\
 , and non-medicalized approach to regulating the volatility of the content
  of the illicit drug market. It not only built upon existing overdose prev
 ention strategies by providing supervised consumption services but also of
 fered rigorously tested cocaine\, heroin\, and methamphetamine\, at cost\,
  to users of these substances.\n&nbsp\;\nThe founders (Eris\, Jeremy) are 
 now facing a potential life in prison. In court\, final arguments are sche
 duled for July 13–21.\nWe are seeking to fund this precarious legal batt
 le against a system that has turned it's back on the many deaths of the fe
 ntanyl crisis.\n&nbsp\;\nBands\, BBQ(??) + Raffle\n&nbsp\;\nReach out to v
 olunteer or help in Raffle\, Organization or Donation:\nhttps://www.zeffy.
 com/en-CA/donation-form/dulf-legal-aid-ii-the-final-push\nsignal @freedulf
 .69\n&nbsp\;\nMore announcements to follow
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/way/352197557
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:resmtl-38
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260615T043340
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260704T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260704T140000
SUMMARY:Punx Picnic - Hochelaga vs Mile End Kickball
LOCATION:(métro Joliette)
DESCRIPTION:2026-07-04 12:00:00\n\n(métro Joliette)\n\nhttps://www.openst
 reetmap.org/way/88541242\n\nMONTREAL PUNKS PICNIC 2026\nDo you like gettin
 g drunk in a park? Does the thought of ingesting veggie dogs and hot PBR w
 hile attempting hand to eye coordination fill you with glee?&nbsp\;\nCome 
 one\, come all\, to Parc Lalancette on July 4 to engage in a time honored 
 tradition passed down from our late friend Steve.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;\nThe after
 noon of debauchery will include\, for those brave enough to engage\, a kic
 kball match where we will pit two rivaling neighborhoods against each othe
 r:\nHOCHELAGA vs MILE END\nFeast: 1pm\nGames: 3pm\nVeggie dawgs for sale. 
 All proceeds to DULF.\nFollowed by an evening of merriment at Foufs with a
  selection of local minstrels.\nhttps://montreal.askapunk.net/event/benefi
 t-gig-for-varning-xviii-vol-ii\nGet off yer ass!\nUp the Punx Tabarnak!
